Oh, just in case the table is very large, you might need to bind the events inside of the `initialized` callback ([demo](https://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/gzysy10p/3/))

```js
$('#table').tablesorter({
  theme: 'blue',
  widgets: ['zebra'],
  data: dataObject,
  initialized: function(table) {
    $(table).on('sortStart', function() {
      alert('ok');
    });
  }
});
```

Hi @PolHaghverdian!

Yes, jQuery Mobile still requires jQuery.

If you need to modify the class names of the table add them to your HTML. Or add a `data-theme` as needed. For tablesorter specific classes, modify the [configuration options](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#Configuration) that start with `css`.

Also make sure to initialize the code using [`pagecreate`](https://api.jquerymobile.com/pagecreate/) instead of a document ready function:

```js
jQuery(document).on("pagecreate", function() { 
  jQuery("table").tablesorter();
});
```

