@VEDA95 `webpack-manifest-plugin`'s `publicPath` member prepends the path to each value.  To create the `{ publicPath: '...', assets: { ... } }` manifest.json that Flask-Webpack expects, you can either  use @nickjj 's [ manifest-revison-plugin ](https://github.com/nickjj/manifest-revision-webpack-plugin) or use the [reduce option](https://www.npmjs.com/package/webpack-manifest-plugin#reduce) to `webpack-manifest-plugin` like this:
```{javascript}
new WebpackManifestPlugin({
  reduce: (manifest, {name, path, isInitial}) => {
      if (isInitial) manifest = {assets: {}, publicPath: 'your publicPath'};
      manifest.assets[name] = path;
      return manifest;
    }
})

// outputs:
// {
//   "assets": {
//     "hello_world.js": "hello_world.7ac9a1a1fe7750b56453.js"
//   },
//   "publicPath": "your publicPath"
// }
```

