@aizvorski There is definite cleanup possible in `colorconv`. That's a really central part of the package, though, so tweaks to it need to be very carefully reviewed. Generally, though, bench it either way and if the tests still pass with the new/faster/more efficient version, that's what should go in. I suspect combining steps like you suggest will be faster.

As far as naming goes, this is one case where we deviate from PEP8 deliberately (and with long history). Matlab names their color conversion routines `xxx2yyy` and early on when building our user base, we were mainly courting Matlab users (still relevant today). So the more _familiar_ the API felt, the easier it was to convince people to see the light. Because that convention has so much momentum in the package, changing it would be a major, disruptive ordeal for pretty much every user.

So my recommendation is two thumbs up to cleaning the code internally, but largely leaving the API as-is.

