I implemented a custom `run_transaction` that uses `execute` directly. Two key insights are: we are running with `autocommit=False` and we call `dbsession.expire_all()` manually before executing our rollback command so the SQLAlchemy object cache is cleared between retry attempts.

The interesting bit of this comment is the `run_transaction` definition, which I hope follows the guidelines given in your documentation. The rest of the code sample is provided to help clarify my approach. In this example I use a `scoped_sesssion` which results in a thread-local `dbsession` variable.

```
class CockroachSession:
    def __init__(self, session):
        self.session = session

    def commit(self):
        self.session.flush()
        self.session.execute("RELEASE SAVEPOINT cockroach_restart")

    def rollback(self):
        # rollback is handled by `run_transaction`
        raise Exception("manual rollback not supported")

    def __getattr__(self, attr):
        return getattr(self.session, attr)


class CockroachSessionFactory(sqlalchemy.orm.session.sessionmaker):
    """Decorate the session objects returned by `sessionmaker` with CockroachSession."""

    def __call__(self, **kwargs):
        session = super().__call__(**kwargs)
        return CockroachSession(session)


log.info('Create database engine.')
_engine = sqlalchemy.create_engine(
    config['SQLALCHEMY_DB_URL'],
    echo=False,
    connect_args=config['SQLALCHEMY_CONNECT_ARGS']
    )
_session_factory = CockroachSessionFactory(bind=_engine, autocommit=True)
dbsession = sqlalchemy.orm.scoped_session(_session_factory)

# Adapted from https://github.com/cockroachdb/cockroach-go/blob/master/crdb/tx.go
def run_transaction(callback):
    with dbsession.begin():
        dbsession.execute("SAVEPOINT cockroach_restart")
        while True:
            try:
                return callback()
            except sqlalchemy.exc.DatabaseError as exc:
                if isinstance(exc.orig, psycopg2.OperationalError):
                    # See https://www.cockroachlabs.com/docs/transactions.html and
                    # https://github.com/cockroachdb/cockroach-go/blob/master/crdb/tx.go#L85
                    ambiguous_error = 'CR000'
                    # Error code '40001' from
                    # https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/static/errcodes-appendix.html#ERRCODES-TABLE
                    retryable_error = psycopg2.errorcodes.SERIALIZATION_FAILURE
                    if exc.orig.pgcode in [ambiguous_error, retryable_error]:
                        # Expire internal object state before retrying the
                        # transaction, so objects are refreshed from
                        # database. This is necessary as rollback is not
                        # automatically called.
                        #
                        # See
                        # http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/latest/orm/session_api.html#sqlalchemy.orm.session.Session.expire_all
                        dbsession.expire_all()
                        dbsession.execute("ROLLBACK TO SAVEPOINT cockroach_restart")
                        continue
                raise
```

