I was bitten by this recently. I foolishly assumed that the helpers would respect `exclude` as I use it to break cycles, but in hindsight I'm not sure it should. From the perspective of Swagger, removing a field changes the model. I suspect the only sane way of resolving your example would be:

```
class FooBaseSchema(Schema):
    bar = fields.Str()

class FooBaseSchema(FooSchema):
    baz = fields.Str()

class BobSchema(Schema):
    foo = fields.Nested(FooBaseSchema)
